inequities as a Superwoman can activate inflammatory markers resulting in a 
weakened immune system, increased cardiovascular risk factors, and a shortened 
life expectancy. This article explores the Superwomen experience and its impact 
on health outcomes, with a focus on minimizing cardiovascular morbidity and 
mortality.

